From c6388fbcc307001bc4d8ce4781c23769db4a887a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: AAP Rebuild <aap-rebuild-bot@localhost>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 16:23:54 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] patch: hub disabled by default (omitted block = disabled)

Flip hub from 'missing block = enabled' to 'missing block = disabled',
matching the existing convention for lightspeed and mcp.

Removes the 'Set hub as enabled if no hub is defined' task. After this
patch:
  - hub: omit block               -> _hub_enabled stays false (skipped)
  - hub: { disabled: true }       -> _hub_enabled stays false
  - hub: { ... no disabled flag } -> _hub_enabled true (existing path)
  - hub: { disabled: false, ... } -> _hub_enabled true (existing path)

Rationale: this fork doesn't ship a hub-operator rebuild and we have no
plans to deploy automation hub. Default-disabled prevents an enabled hub
from registering a ServiceCluster row at gateway init that has no
backing operator (would force the 4-step component-removal recipe).

Aligns the asymmetric component-enable rules in determine_if_enabled.yml:
  - Default-enabled: controller, eda
  - Default-disabled: hub, lightspeed, mcp
---
 roles/common/tasks/determine_if_enabled.yml | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/roles/common/tasks/determine_if_enabled.yml b/roles/common/tasks/determine_if_enabled.yml
index 21563fc..9a03cc1 100644
--- a/roles/common/tasks/determine_if_enabled.yml
+++ b/roles/common/tasks/determine_if_enabled.yml
@@ -19,11 +19,6 @@
     - hub is defined
     - hub.disabled is not defined or not hub.disabled
 
-- name: Set hub as enabled if no hub is defined
-  ansible.builtin.set_fact:
-    _hub_enabled: true
-  when: hub is not defined
-
 - name: Determine if eda is enabled (existing or new)
   ansible.builtin.set_fact:
     _eda_enabled: true
